  "texts": [
    "The model was trained on only 304 images across eight classes, which may not be sufficient for capturing each class's variability.",
    "Some microfossils are derived from land plants, and DL has been successfully utilised for classification of such specimens (refer to Table 10).",
    "Andriopoulou et al. (2023) implement a DL architecture that integrates a pre-trained MobileNetV2 as the encoder and a U-Net as the decoder, leveraging the strengths of both models for the classification and segmentation of phytoliths (silica structures found in some plant tissues).",
    "The use of depthwise separable convolutions within MobileNetV2 is novel, which significantly reduces the number of parameters and computational load, making it well-suited for the limited dataset used.",
    "The encoder-decoder structure, with maintained skip connections, allows the model to retain spatial details, enhancing segmentation accuracy."
